---

Ember bundles the following open source components:

- OpenMM (MIT/LGPL) - https://openmm.org
- AMBER Force Fields ff14SB, ff19SB (Public Domain, UCSF)
- OPC Water Model (Izadi et al. 2014)
- OpenFF Sage 2.0 (MIT) - https://openforcefield.org
- OpenMM Force Fields (MIT) - https://github.com/openmm/openmmforcefields
- openmm-metal (MIT/LGPL) - https://github.com/philipturner/openmm-metal
- VkFFT (MIT) - https://github.com/DTolm/VkFFT
- RDKit (BSD-3-Clause) - https://rdkit.org
- Open Babel (GPL-2.0) - https://openbabel.org
- PDBFixer (MIT) - https://github.com/openmm/pdbfixer
- MDAnalysis (GPL-2.0) - https://mdanalysis.org
- AmberTools (LGPL) - https://ambermd.org/AmberTools.php
- NGL Viewer (MIT) - https://nglviewer.org
- Electron (MIT) - https://electronjs.org
- SolidJS (MIT) - https://solidjs.com

Note: Open Babel and MDAnalysis are GPL-2.0 licensed and are invoked as
separate processes, not linked into Ember's application code.
